story: Jill was playing video games with her sister. Jill was angry that she was losing every game. Jill took her game controller and threw it at the TV. The TV screen cracked right down the center. Jill and her sister could not play any more videogames.

Nila's mom was diagnosed with stage four cancer. Nila knew her mom did not have a long time to live. Nila made sure to provide her mom with a good life until her death. Nila fostered many good memories with her mom and they were happy. Nila loved her mom.

Lita wanted to watch her favorite show on television. Her kids insisted that she sit down to watch it with them. Lita told them that she had chores to do. Her kids dragged her laundry basket to the living room. Lita folded the laundry while watching television.

It snowed so hard that school was called off for the day. The boys put on their coats, hats, gloves and boots and went outside. They built a tall snowman and a snow fort. They had a snowball fight. They went inside to roast marshmallows.
Neil was backpacking Europe. He had just arrived in Dover. He loved how friendly the people were! He also loved their delicious food. Neil was having a great time.

Dave gathered up all of his beach gear. He took the day off just so he could spend it on the beach. When he went outside he discovered it was much to dark. The sky was full of black storm clouds. Dave was so disappointed!

Jesus spent the day polishing the furniture. As night approached he surveyed the work he'd done. Everything looked shiny and new. Jesus invited all of his friends over for a party that evening. They said his furniture looked nice.

A new Chick-Fil-A just opened up and I couldn't wait to try it. The line was out the door. I waited for a half hour just to order something. I ordered a spicy chicken sandwich. Right then I decided this was my new favorite food.

Frank did not want to do his homework. He wanted to play video games instead. Frank's parents told him to do his homework first. Frank threw a tantrum and got punished. Frank lost his video games for a week.

It was Friday night so I decided to rent a movie. I headed down to a Redbox to get one. After taking an hour to decide I finally picked The Departed. I got home and made some snacks, then went to put the movie in. It was the best movie I had seen in a long time.

Tia wanted to make something to sell at the craft fair. She decided to make homemade soap. She made glycerin soap in a big pot on her kitchen stove. Then she pressed flower blossoms into the centers of her bars. Tia then made pretty labels to put on each bar.

Grace always loved playing tricks on the teacher. Her favorite trick was to hide all of the chalk from the teacher. One day as she was hiding the chalk, the teacher caught Grace. She was suspended from school for two weeks. Grace decided to stop playing tricks at school.

One year, Matt was training for a half marathon. Near the time of the race, he slipped on a run and damaged his knee. Matt missed the race and required an extensive rehab. As soon as he could, Matt was back to training. His training paid off at a marathon later that year.

Six year old Bobby wanted a cat very badly. His parents didn't say no but they weren't excited about it either. One morning a friendly young cat showed up at their door. Bobby was very excited when his mom said it could come inside. Bobby was overjoyed when his mother said the cat could stay.

Holly asked her brother to put suntan lotion on her back. He took his time and applied it very carefully. Later that day, Holly wondered why people were laughing. She later realized her brother had made a design with the lotion. Holly yelled at her brother to get back at him.
I always try to go to bed on time. Last night I was hooked watching a new tv show. Before I knew it it was really late. I should have been asleep hours ago. The television show had hooked me in.

I hired a social media manager. I thought they would drive more traffic to my website. They spent most of their time reading other people's posts. My traffic actually went down in the following month. I decided to fire my new social media manager.

Solomon didn't like his first name. He thought that it was too old-fashioned. At a job interview, the interviewer praised his name. Solomon suspected that his being hired was related to his unique name. Solomon thought his name might not be so bad after all.

Bob and Jim were playing ball in the house one day. They knocked over the vase and it broke into many pieces. They were afraid their mom would get angry at them. They found some glue, and carefully glued the vase back together. The glue held the vase together and their mom never found out.

I was walking to the store recently. As I was passing an exit, I felt cold, hard steel on my arm. I was shocked that I was being hit by a car! The driver was very apologetic after he saw I was hit. I told them it was okay and then walked away.
Emily took her child to the zoo. The saw many animals, including lions. Her child was very afraid of the lions. He started to scream and cry. Emily picked up her child to comfort him.
Yolanda hates roller coasters. Katie does not understand why. She decided to force Yolanda to ride one with her. Yolanda vomited all over Katie. Katie regretted forcing Yolanda to go on the ride.

My friend Sharon was nervous yesterday. She found out her company wanted her to retire. Although she has a good pension, she was still nervous. I helped her rewrite her resume, preparing for a job search. Sharon is now looking forward to a new chapter in her life.

It was my first time skiing and I was not doing well. I skied directly in the path of another skier. We collided and both fell to the ground. The other skier told me his name was Jack and it was nice to meet me. I thought Jack was very polite.

Kelly went down to the ocean to relax. She immediately went and put her feet in. As she put her feet in however, the wave captured her. Her clothes got soaked. Kelly went home to change into dry clothes.

Jaime wanted to ask jack to go to the school dance with her. After school she waited for jack outside of the front door. When jack was exiting he was walking hand in hand with another girl. Jaime froze unable to speak. Jaime then told him that they were through.
I was looking for a nice painting for my living room. Hence yesterday I went out looking. I finally found a beautiful one I loved. The painting was of a waterfall. I purchased it and brought it home.

A boy Jack had been asking his parents to get a puppy for months. After all the time he asked they finally gave in and said yes. Jack spent about thirty minutes looking online for a puppy. He found one in the area that he lived. Jack then showed the online puppy and pleaded with them to get it.

Renee was inspired by the music of Eddie Van Halen. She decided to learn to play guitar. She bought an electric guitar and an amp. She hated pressing the strings with her fingers. Renee decided she would have to get used to it.

Ora had been dared not to shower in order to join a sorority. She couldn't imagine going without clean water for a week! Then she thought of a loophole. They hadn't said Ora couldn't take a bath! Ora took a bath.

Amber had been working a lot lately. It was stressing her out a great deal due to other personal issues. She had been dying for a day off to relax. On her day off she hung out with boyfriend Rob They relaxed all day and Amber felt much better.
The kids went to the graveyard. The came upon a grave with chains. Some of the chains had been broken. They became scared and ran. They didn't want to go there again.

In the autumn, Susan planted some flower seeds in the backyard. Over the course of the winter, she had forgotten about planting them. Once April came, little flowers appeared all over the backyard. To protect the new garden from her dog, she decided to fence it in. Soon, Susan had a beautiful garden.
Sue's cat was nowhere to be seen. Sue searched for her cat for hours until she heard purring outside. Her cat was stuck in the tree. Sue called up the fire department. Suzi's cat was saved.

Today we went on a plane ride. The plane was very big, I was scared. When we got on the plane Mom told me it will be fun. The plane made a lot of loud noises but it wasn't too bad. I am no longer afraid of planes.

Ariel is our 5 month old baby. She had woke up the other morning extremely fussy. We couldn't figure out what was wrong at first. We then seen a fresh tooth popping through her gum line. We had a week of hell as her tooth came in.

Earl is a grandfather for the first time today! His daughter just had her first baby and she had a girl. Earl has secretly been saving money for his new granddaughter. He surprise his daughter with a new savings account for her child. His daughter now adds to it, for her daughter's college.

Gina was at her friend Ruth's house. A girl she didn't know named Jane showed up. Jane was rude, and stuck up. Gina later discovered Jane was her enemy Joe's sister. So now she avoids Jane all the time.

Lilly made cranberry sauce for Thanksgiving. It was her first time meeting her boyfriend's parents. The meal was going well until she took a bite of what she had made. She realized she had forgotten to put sugar in it. The cranberry sauce was very sour.

JJ played all day long. When evening came, he was tired. He nearly fell asleep in his bath, and his mother said it was bedtime. His mother put him in pajamas, took him to his bed, and sang to him. He fell asleep.

Gina was in trouble for something her sister did. Her parents held her accountable since she was older. Gina thought this was very unfair. She went to her room and sat alone, waiting for an apology. Her sister came and apologized.

Jan had to pick up her daughter after class. In a hurry, she drove to school in housecoat and slippers. Jan waited in the car for her daughter, who didn't show up. Worried, Jan went to the door of the class to find her daughter. Then she realized it was Saturday.

Joe was an amateur prospector. He went out in the hills to look for gold. Instead of gold, he found many small blue and green stones. He gathered them all up to be appraised in town. Joe hoped they were valuable.
Robbie wanted to buy a new hat. He drove an hour just to get the new hat he wanted. Finally when he got there he got the last one. When he tried it on it fit perfectly. He wore it everyday.
Today was Iris's fifth birthday! Her mom had planned her a surprise party. All of her friends were there. She opened presents and had cake. Iris had a lot of fun at her party.

Rene was at the arcade with a couple of friends on a Friday night. He was getting ready to play a game but realized he forgot his wallet. His friend Jack noticed this and offered to let him borrow money. Rene appreciated his offer and took him up on it. Rene then played games.
I wrote an ebook that needed a cover. I made several book covers in Photoshop. I shared my creations with several people. I asked people to vote for Cover A or Cover B. Most people liked Cover A.

Suzy went to the ice cream store. She ordered a vanilla milkshake. When she tried to pay the man for her milkshake, he smiled at her. He told her that she won a special contest. He gave her the milkshake for free.

Beth was taking a shower when she heard a loud knock on the door. She didn't want to answer and waited for it to go away. The next time she took a shower, she heard the loud knock again. But when she rushed out of the shower to answer, no one was there. Beth decided she was hearing things.

Gina's sister cut her ankle on broken glass. The blood ran down her foot and into her shoe. When she saw the blood she ran home. Gina ran behind her, but couldn't keep up. Gina's sister went to the doctor.

Jake is one of my roommates. He took a gap year last year to work as a chef in Australia. Since the dining hall food was subpar we decided to cook. He taught me how to cook and season a steak. Jake has kept all of us well-fed all year.

Amy was very stressed out all the time. A friend suggested that she try meditation. Amy was skeptical, but she agreed to give it a shot. She went to a class and breathed and focused. It helped her mental state immensely.
Lia went to England. She took a bus tour. The tour stopped at Stonehenge. Lia got out of the bus to look. Lia took many photos of Stonehenge.

I took gymnastics as a child. I was learning the balance beam and doing moves on it. As I did a round off flipping off the beam, I landed wrong. I broke my ankle and was in so much pain! I was rushed to the hospital.

A little boy was in the third grade. He was very smart but struggled with reading. Whenever he read out loud his classmates laughed at him. He started to practice reading every single day. At the end of the year, he did well on his reading test.

Cindy was at a restaurant. And she ordered hot soup. But the waitress forgot to tell her that the bowl was hot. So when received the bowl from the waitress, she hurt her hands. Cindy went and ran cold water over her hands.

Leah is a full time college student who wants a part time job. Leah searches craigslist and finds an entry level position. Leah applies and the next day get a call for an interview. Leah goes to the interview and does really well. Leah gets the job.
My laptop didn't want to work. It stopped turning on for some reason. I tried a few different things to fix it. Finally I got a new charger off the internet. Now it comes on every time.

Cristin went to a music festival. One of Kristin's favorite bands should be performing at the festival. She found out that her favorite band's performance was cancelled. Cristin is frustrated that she did not get to see their performance. Cristin decided not to go to the festival next year.

Stewart tried to finish his favorite task before going to bed. He got so engrossed in it, he forgot to keep the fire going. Shivering, he pulled a bunch of blankets around himself. He became very warm and content. When he woke up it was freezing.

We decided we would learn to make candy. We checked out a book on the subject and read up. Then, we set to work trying. We realized greatly overestimated how hard it was to make candy. We found we made a mess in the kitchen.

Jane's girlfriend works at a flower shop. She never gets tired of her work. One day Jane decided to get her a rose. Even though her girlfriend saw many a day she loved it. Jane's girlfriend was a die-hard flower lover.
Matt was out for a walk with his mom. Suddenly he saw something shiny on the ground. He bent to pick it up. It was a gold ring! Matt was excited to be so lucky.
Teresa was an artist. She made a beautiful sculpture of an angel. She entered it into an art contest. The judges liked the sculpture very much. She won the contest and was proud of herself.

When I first met Janice, she didn't know how to crack a walnut. I couldn't believe she had gotten this far in life without this skill. I offered to teach her many methods to crack nuts. She accepted. Janice is now an expert walnut cracker.

Rufus has just enrolled in a new school and he has no friends there. At first he feels apprehensive and worried he won't meet anyone. However, a nice guy named Ralph introduces himself to Rufus one day. They realize that they are in the same Chemistry class. They decide to be lab partners in their class together.

Emile wanted to be a great chef. He took lessons and worked hard learning how to cook. He practiced his cooking and served food for friends. His friends loved his cooking and encouraged him. Emile eventually got a job as a chef.

Joe was helping his dad clear the woods in the back of their yard. All of a sudden he heard loud buzzing. He had stirred up a bee's nest. He got stung six times before he could escape. Joe was angry he got hurt.

Lester has always loved academic debate. He decides to found a debate team at his college. He finds a professor to advise the team, and slowly recruits students. Soon the team is large enough to debate another school. The other school wins by a huge margin over Lester's team.
My aunt is a nurse. She often talks about long hours at work. Last week was especially bad. She didn't have a single day where she didn't work late. It was hard work.

I approached the front of my school. Since my brother was at work, I had to wait for him to pick me up. Several hours later, I was impatiently waiting. He eventually came before night time. I was very angry at him for not picking me up earlier.

Josh was writing short stories for a researcher. The researcher was impressed by Josh's stories. The researcher decided to give Josh a bonus. Josh was happy that he got a bonus. Josh used the bonus to repair his broken car.

When I was a kid, Google started for the first time. I remember asking my dad how to use the site. He showed me how to type and search anything I wanted. I became enthralled, and spent every day at my desk having fun. I learned a lot from Google.
James loved to challenge himself physically. He decided to begin training for a marathon. James began running every day before work. Finally James ran the marathon. James finished in the top 50.
Phil went for a walk in the park. It was a warm breezy day. He ran into a few friends along his walk. One of them offered him a drink. Phil was thirsty and accepted the drink.

Flora's tooth started to hurt. She hated the dentist, so she tried to ignore it. The pain got worse and worse. Finally, Flora had to call for a dentist appointment. The dentist was able to make her tooth feel better.
Sean came over today. Sam, Sean, and I played games. They started to get mad at me about how bad I was. They said I couldn't play anymore until I got better. I was really hurt.

My son bought a drum set for his one year old niece last fall. The set had drumsticks, a cymbal, and a seat. His niece lives in NYC. She saw it when she visited, and was thrilled. She wanted to play the drums.

Josiah was a baby who was trying to crawl for the first time. To help him, his mother put out an exciting toy that jingled. As she made the toy rattle, Josiah became very interested. He started groping the ground and inching towards his mom. Josiah crawled to his mother and took the toy.

Kelly and her friends decided to go to Indian for lunch. They were the first ones inside the restaurant. It was a buffet so they got what they wanted. The girls loved the food. They returned many times.

May was Harry's favorite month. Harry had his birthday in May and school also let out. Every May Harry would also go to the country to see his friend Mary. Mary and Harry got engaged eventually. Harry loved Mary.

My friend wants to be a doctor, so she took the MCAT. The first time she took it, she did not get a good enough score. She studied very hard and took it again. This time, she did very well! We took her out to drinks to celebrate.
At a party on Friday everyone decided to play musical chairs. The game involved dozens of people. Eventually it was narrowed down to two. It was two girls. The tall, brown haired girl won the game.

Marco is starting a new job today. He wants to look good on his first day. Marco decides to put on a necktie. His new boss is impressed with how good he looks. Marco is glad that he made a good impression.

Rosie's class was having a little party. She decided to make a fruit salad for everyone. She spent lots of money on the fruit and lots of time preparing it. On the day of the party she scooped a huge bowl of the fruit salad up. Rosie's class shared the fruit salad.

Ben walked along the street and found the end of a length of string. He picked it up and pulled on it. More string came but not the end. Ben followed the string to see where it went. Ben was fascinated by the string.

Timmy loves watching cartoons. His parents don't let him watch unless he does his chores. Today's chore is to clean his room. Timmy's room is a mess. Timmy spent all day cleaning so he could watch tv.

Caroline was a student in medical school. Caroline worked very hard to get good grades. One day Caroline failed a test by one point. Caroline was very frustrated but she continued to study hard. Later, she passed the test.
Neil flew into Russia. There, he visited tourist sites and saw friendly locals. He found that Russia was colorful and vibrant. It also had a great and rich history. Neil found the trip stimulating.

Amy wanted to get a manicure. She went to the nail salon near her job. The lady finished and asked if she wanted fingernail polish as well. Amy chose a bright red nail polish color. Amy loved bright colors.

Tim decided to spend more time with his granddad. His grandpa loved birdwatching, so Tim watched with him. They marked their sightings in a notebook. Soon Tim was really interested! Tim and his grandad found a hobby that they both enjoyed.

Harry loved hockey. He decided to sign up to play for a local league. Harry attended the tryouts for the team. Harry hoped he did well enough to make the team. A few days later, Harry heard that he made the team.
Maggie wanted to paint her room. She wanted to have a pink room. She ask her mom to buy her paint. The next day Maggie painted her room. Maggie loved the color pink.

When I was younger, I went to summer camp. We had a lot of fun playing games with the counselors. My favorite thing to do was play cards. The camp counselors knew so many different card games. My favorite card game was poker.

Sal was nervous on his first day of high school. And as he sat in class, he felt intimidated by his peers. At lunch time, another student approached him. And that student felt the same way as Sal. Sal found out he wasn't alone.

Trudey wanted to write novels for a living. She wrote one through traditional publishing means. It barely made enough to cover the advance she had received. She wrote another through self-publishing avenues. Trudey hoped self-publishing would be more profitable.
My mother used to have a pet goat. She took very good care of it. One day, she realized the goat was missing. She asked her mother where it was. Katie was relieved when her mother said the back yard.
Anna had been tending her garden all summer. She went outside to harvest. All her fruits and veggies were ready! She picked them one by one. She had a bountiful harvest.

Tom liked to look at old cars. For his birthday, his family got him tickets to a classic car museum. Tom thought it was a wonderful gift. His family accompanied him to the museum. Tom loved his time at the museum.

Morris buys himself a skateboard to stay active. He brings the skateboard to the park for a day of skateboarding. He notices that he is much older than the other people there. However, they welcome him, and they don't seem to mind his age. The younger skaters taught Morris a lot of tricks.

Jeremy's mother didn't approve of his lifestyle. When he was 21, Jeremy decided to move out. He found an apartment in a nearby state with a new job. After several Years he cleaned up, and finances his own life. Jeremy enjoyed being more responsible.
Christian's school was starting football tryouts. Christian decided to try out for the team. He practiced every day. He tried out for the team. Christian got on the team.

Carlos has always wanted to visit France. He decides that he should learn to speak French before he goes. He enrolls in a night class and studies very hard. Finally Carlos can speak French pretty well. Carlos makes the most of his French on his trip to Paris.

Amelia decided to take a vacation to Mexico. She booked her flight and hotel. When she got to Mexico, she was sure to visit many different things. She loved every moment of it. Amelia decided to vacation to Mexico more often.

Last week the internet went out. My wife and I were bored out of our minds. Every other option available seemed boring. Eventually we just drank and talked for a while. We ended up having a fun time after all.

I was walking to the mall. Someone was calling me and I decided to pull out my phone. I had a hard time getting it out since my pockets were tight. The phone ended up jumping out of my pocket. I almost cracked my phone.
My family wanted a pet. We went to the pet store on Saturday. We saw lots of dogs and kittens. We fell in love with a cute black kitten. We bought the kitten.

My husband and I rented a car on vacation. The car we got was horrible. The wipers didn't work, and a headlight was out. It smelled awful and was very dirty. We will never rent from that car company again.

Jimmy grew up very poor. However, his parents always did his best to provide for him. When he got into a good college, they worked two jobs to afford it. When he graduated, he wanted to show his appreciation. So he repaid them for college.

Sarah always had a fascination with the night sky. Noticing her passion, Sarah's father bought her a new telescope. She was ecstatic. She went outside every night to diligently view the night sky. Sarah loved her new telescope.

Keri was babysitting her niece on a weekday. She needed to put her to sleep early. Unfortunately the niece had too much energy. Keri convinced her to do exercises with her. Then Keri took the child for  a  walk  to tire her out.

Anthony wanted to learn how to speak Spanish. He found an online Spanish course, and he enrolled. Anthony studied hard, and eventually he learned the language. Anthony speaks Spanish fluently now. Anthony became successful because of his linguistic abilities.
Last night I attended a cocktail party. I wore my new white dress. Everyone at the party loved it. However to my dismay I spilled wine all over it. I was so angry at myself!

It was summer and Gina and her sister were bored. They decided to watch music videos. There was the music video channel or the black entertainment channel. They chose to watch the black entertainment channel. Gina and her sister had a great time together.

Julie loved to read anything she could get her hands on. Most of her time was spent in the library. Her favorite library was staffed by Miss Watson. Miss Watson saw Julie's love of books and offered her a job. Julie happily accepted!
Mark was running late to work. He tried to get their on time by driving over the speed limit. A traffic cop pulled him over. He was given a speeding ticket. Mark ended up being late for work.

Mark had a big interview for a new job. He prepared himself for the questions they may ask. The interviewer seemed to be impressed with Mark's answers. The interviewer informed Mark he had the job. Mark was very happy.

Kristen was tired of her room. She need to move it around for a change. She hadn't moved it in over four Year's. After moving everything she saw a huge stain where her bed covered. She decided to put a rug over the stain.

I remember the scariest haunted house I've ever been to. It was an old, rickety, uninhabited house that was made for scares. The house was scary in itself. The scariest part was at the end. A witch jumped out and gave me the fright of my life.

Ray and his friends planned to go to the beach. So Ray worked out to build up his muscles. When Ray and his friends went to the beach, they noticed Ray's body. Ray was happy to be the center of attention. All his friends were jealous of his new physique.

Max was a very bright boy. But he would become lost in his own vivid imagination. No matter how hard he tried, he found himself daydreaming. Max did not do very well in school. Max consistently failed.

Yesterday Kim got a brand new blazer. To her delight, when she got to school everyone complimented her on it. The next few weeks, Kim saw that everyone was wearing the blazer. She felt happy to start a new trend. Kim was glad people were inspired to imitate her.

Timmy was caught with unpaid parking tickets. He didn't have enough money to pay for them. Instead he had to be arrested and jailed for two days. He lost his jobs for missing work. Timmy then had to find another job,

Carl looked into a telescope for the first time at 9-Year's-old. He was immediately breath-taken and full of wonder. He decided he had to learn more about the cosmos. He studied science and astronomy through high school and college. He ended up becoming a scientist.
Neil was visiting Romania. He had just arrived and was excited to see Transylvania. When he got there, he saw gorgeous old castles. He also found friendly locals. Neil enjoyed visiting Transylvania.

Aya wanted to be a model. She thought she had a chance since she was thin and pretty. So she entered her town's annual modeling contest. To her shock, she won the contest. Aya was very happy about the outcome of the contest.

Tom was at the bus stop on a weekend. Next to him was a tall gentleman. He started yelling all of a sudden. Tom and everyone else around him got a bit uncomfortable. Tom asked him what the problem was.

Boris was addicted to video games. His mother was concerned. She called a psychologist to get help. The psychologist tried to convince Boris to stop his addiction. Boris realized he was wasting his life.

Mia had never tried falafel. She didn't think she would like it. However, her friends talked her into trying it. She realized it was delicious! Mia liked it so much she decided to learn how to make it.
Laura had a passion for art. She would paint everyday after class. She painted a self portrait of herself one day. She posted it online for everyone to see. Laura was pleased to show people her art.

A man went to design the tallest tower in the world. He drew plans to make it twice as high as the current tallest. He took the plans to a developer to build. The developer asked him how tall to build the tower. The man built the tower and it was grand.
Jon loved the night sky. He would spend many of his nights looking at the stars. His mom saw that he loved the night sky. His mom bought him a telescope. Jon used his telescope often.

I decided to add a new fountain pen to my collection. I'd seen online videos of a nice pen called a Pelikan M800. So I went to the pen shop at my local mall. The shop had just the model of pen I wanted. I bought the pen.

Beth was recovering from an illness. She was finally able to eat food after 4 days. Although she was better she wasn't well. She decided to take Friday off from school and take time to heal. Beth needed to rest.
Kira always loved Japanese culture. Many of her favorite movies were in Japanese. She decided that she would travel there. For Years she saved money for her trip. It was the best trip of her life.

Jim's car was ten Year's old, and started having problems. He decided to trade it in and buy a new one. He did a lot of research on the most economical cars to buy. He decided on one that could also run on a battery. Jim saved a lot of money in gas by buying a battery run car.

Michael likes to go to the beach but has trouble swimming. During a beach trip his friends made a dare to him. They told him to go into deep water and he did. Michael got tired when he was out and started to yell for help. His friends helped him back to the shore.
Fred always stopped at the same coffee shop before work. He got to know the attractive barista. He developed a crush on her. Finally Fred worked up the courage to ask her on a date. She said yes.

Sarah had never been on a boat before. Today her mom took her to the pier for her very first boat ride. Sarah was very excited. She stepped on the boat and heard the engine roar. She loved every minute of it.
Bob wanted a hamburger. But he also wanted to eat healthier. So he decided to make a veggie burger. Bob thought it wasn't as good as a normal burger. Bob went out to McDonald's later that evening.

Gina decided to bake an apple pie for the first time. She was extremely careful to follow the recipe exactly. After putting the pie in the oven, she eagerly waited to try it. It turned out to be delicious! She shared the recipe and the pie with all her friends.

Gill's favorite character was Columbo portrayed by Peter Falk. Gill had seen every episode. Gill even owned all of them, including the many later seasons. Gill started acting like Columbo sometimes. Her attempts at solving murders, however, were less successful.

Mia loved being outdoors. One summer, she decided to go mountain climbing. She joined a club of people who climbed mountains together. They climbed the tallest mountain in her area. Mia had a great time.

Cara went to a food cart in Philadelphia the other day. She stopped by an amazing falafel cart. The food was amazing. Cara couldn't believe how good it was. Cara decided to eat at the food cart every week.

Peter was excited to go to the Sanders rally in New Hampshire. As Peter entered the arena it was full of thousands of people. When Peter saw Bernie he cheered as loudly as possible. He felt thrilled to be there. He couldn't wait to vote for him.

Madeline was thrilled to get a new purse at Saks. Her mother took her to the bag department. Madeline immediately saw a pink bag she loved. She could not believe how amazing it was. Madeline's mother happily bought the bag for her.

Jake's dad took him to his first football game. They got there early and had really good seats. They ate hot dogs and drank soda as well! Jake even saw his favorite player during the game! Jake had a great time at the football game with his dad.

Paulo had always wanted to serve in his student council. However, he was worried he wouldn't be elected. Paulo asked many students for their support in the election. Finally on election day, Paulo was elected to student council. Paulo felt proud of his accomplishment.
Neil had just arrived in Iran. He was enthralled with the cities and countryside. He thought the mountains were so beautiful. The language and people were wonderful too. He was happy to be in Iran.

Barry was excited that he finally registered to vote. He went to the polling place near his home. While walking into the building he noticed all of the campaign signs. He already knew how he would cast his votes. Barry voted.

Ricky fell while hiking in the woods. He was terrified! He thought he had fallen into a patch of poison ivy. Then he used his nature guide to identify the plant. He was relieved to find out he was wrong.
Today was the first day of school. I got to wear my new outfit that Mom bought. I met a lot of new friends. My favorite class is music. I had a great time at school.
Our team had a football game today. We were all pumped to win. We got on the field and practiced before the game. Our team was unified, and worked together. Our team felt gratified.

Rex has always wanted to visit Argentina. He saves up his money for the big trip. Finally he has booked his flight to Argentina. He eats delicious food and drinks many types of wine. Rex enjoys himself.

My friend and I decided to start a band and perform for our families. I was singer and my friend played guitar. We practiced in my garage. Eventually, we got pretty good. We performed a small show for our families the next weekend.

Nora wanted to go on vacation. She decided to visit the mountain cabin. The cabin was beautiful, set in the woods, beside a stream. Nora loved to picnic by the stream. She spread out a blanket and had a lovely picnic.

It was the last day of our vacation. We were eating lunch on the patio of the hotel. We laughed and smiled because it was a great vacation. Then we packed our bags and drove to the airport. We want to revisit someday.

Tyler wanted to have a balloon party with tons of balloons. He and his friends and his parents blew up the balloons. He and his friends played with the balloons and had a lot of fun. They got tired and watched a movie and had dinner. It had been a very fun day.

Lester was proud that he had spent Years without a cell phone. He liked to think he was less dependent on technology than others. However, one day his car had a flat tire and he wished he had a phone. He did not want to have an experience like that again. Lester went out and got the best cell phone he could afford.

I've always wanted to be able to bike thirty miles at one time. Right now I can only bike about twenty miles at once. I got myself a biking trainer who helped me make progress. I worked hard for a few months and ate all the right foods. Now I can bike 30 miles.

It was the second match of the volleyball season. Amy was hopeful she would get a chance to play. After the first game they were ahead. Her coach put her in the game. She finally got her chance to play in the match.

Martha was a terrible cook and her boyfriend knew it. He introduced her to cooking shows and watched them with her. She would practice things she learned on the shows. As the days went by her cooking began to slowly get better. After a while, everything Martha cooked was delicious.
Nina wanted a nice Halloween costume. But she could not afford anything fancy. She looked through her house for ideas. Then she found a great costume for free. Nina was excited.

A police officer came down with the flu today. He was unable to go into work as he could barely get out of bed. His wife spent time taking care of him and making sure he was okay. He made sure to drink enough and eat enough. The police officer eventually got better.

George had an internship. He really wanted to get a full time job with the company. George worked hard and proved to be smart. A position opened up that George wanted. He eagerly applied for it and was ultimately hired.

Sally was on her work break. She went to get tacos from the taco stand outside. She realized she had forgotten her wallet at home. A nice man noticed what happened and offered to pay. Sally was grateful for his kindness.

One summer my sister and I set up a lemonade stand. It was the first month at a new house and we didn't know anyone. Few people walked by and even fewer stopped. The old pastor walked over from next door. He bought lemonade and made us feel welcome in the neighborhood.
Rashid was an excellent car driver. One day Rashid's brother was late for work. Rashid offered to drive his brother. They got there with time to spare. His brother was grateful.
It was  my final performance in marching band. I was playing the snare drum in the band. We played Thriller and Radar Love. The performance was flawless. I was very proud of my performance.
David was an all around great football player. He was nervous about his next game. A scout would be there. This game would determine his future. David hoped to play really well.

Last week I had to give a big speech. I never prepared and only new the very basics. I figured i would just go in and fake it. I used big words and tried to sound smart. It worked and the speech was received well.

Jessica wanted a pony for her birthday more than anything. In the days coming up to it, she asked her dad for a pony. He said he would think about it. He gave Jessica a pony shaped box on her special day. Jessica was disappointed because she wanted a real pony.

Mark notices that his teeth are beginning to hurt one day. He decides to visit his dentist to see what is the matter. The dentist tells Mark that he needs to have his wisdom teeth removed. Mark agrees to have the surgery done. Mark hoped the procedure would stop his dental pain.

Some friends and I made a Counter-Strike team. We practiced a lot for an upcoming tournament. We got to the tournament and went over strategies. We played a tough 6 games. We felt pleased with our performance.

Bill wanted to lose weight. He had been trying for Years, but lacked initiative. He finally stopped being so hard on himself. Growing in confidence, he met  his goals every week. He finally got down to his ideal weight.
Fred had his first karate tournament yesterday. He was very nervous. When it got there he was shaking. Thankfully he ended up doing well. He came in second place.

Yu Darvish is a pitcher for the Texas Rangers. For the last two seasons he has been injured. According to reports, he is finally healthy and able to play. Ranger fans are hopeful he will be a leader for their pitchers. Ranger fans are looking forward to his return.

Anna went to the salon. She was getting her nails done for the first time. She was nervous, but the tech was friendly. He did her nails quickly and expertly. Anna felt very fashionable when she left the salon.

Shari was worried. Her wedding was tomorrow, and it was an outdoor ceremony. But rain was forecast! Thankfully, the wedding day dawned clear and sunny after all. The festivities went on without a hitch.

Joe really wanted to attend Columbia University. He worked really hard in school, was on the soccer team. He got put on the waiting list. Although he was disappointed, he tried his best to the very end. Joe was still very proud of his hard work.

Harry went to the theme park with his family. His dad and brother rode on a big roller coaster with him. He then rode on some smaller rides with his mom. The family ate at a restaurant at the park. Harry had a great time at the park.
Pam's house was where the party was. Everyone bought gifts. Pam bought a cake. Everyone danced and had fun! Pam was a good hostess.

We went to Frank Pepe's pizza shop three weeks ago. The chain is quite famous in Connecticut. The chain recently opened in Boston. We went early to beat the crowd. We had a great pizza at Frank Pepe's pizza shop.

Amy woke up extra hungry today. Unfortunately, she also woke up very late. She rushed around the house and had no time for breakfast. When she made it to work, she realized her coworker brought breakfast! She was so grateful and promised to pay her coworker back.

Tara preferred big band music to all alternatives. She loved all the horns and other brass instruments involved. She tried to find fellow big band lovers. Her attempts were futile. Tara still enjoyed listening on her own!

Joe felt confident going into his boxing match. He dominated the first four rounds. He got hit with a left hook that cut his eye in the fifth. The last seven rounds were a back and forth affair. Joe eventually won the fight.

Nick was challenged to a volleyball match. His girlfriend bet him five dollars she could beat him. Nick did not intend to let her win! He played hard and mercilessly. Nick beat his girlfriend and she gave him the five dollars.

Mark was starting a new job the next day. He was nervous about being around so many strangers. He barely slept any the night before due to anxiety. When he entered the building he was greeted warmly by many people. He realized he would fit in perfectly at the new job.

Tyler has been unemployed for Years. He has spent the last few months diligently applying for work. However, all of his applications are rejected. The rejections contribute to Tyler's feelings of desperation. He realizes he might have to apply for public assistance.

Sean's roommates notice that his clothes and bed start to smell. They tell him he needs to clean his laundry pretty soon. Sean protests at first, but finally he cleans his laundry. His roommates are grateful that Sean no longer smells as bad. They tell him to never wait so long to do laundry again.

Gregory took a pottery class at a nearby night school. He was terrible at sculpture. He grew to like throwing pots on pottery wheels very much. Eventually he was making pots half as tall as he was. He was very proud of his pots.

Gary was a brave child. One day he decided to climb over the fence in his backyard. His parents looked all over for him. They found him sitting on the swing at the park. Gary's parents were relieved to find him.

Gina liked to volunteer at a homeless shelter. She had spent Years going there for many hours a week. The staff decided to do something to show their appreciation. They chipped in and got Gina a gift. Gina was so touched she cried when they gave it to her.

Bev had been studying very hard. She couldn't wait for the weekend. When it came, she slept in very late. Then she got up and went out to party. By Sunday night, Bev was exhausted again.

Maybelle's breath always smelled like peppermints. Her house did as well, or at least that's what he remembers. To this day he keeps peppermints in his cupboards. They remind him of his grandma and what she meant to him. It is a fond memory.
Oliver needed a new radio. He didn't know anything about them, though. He had a friend help him pick one out. The friend was a pro and found him a good deal. Oliver was grateful to his friend.

Gina realized she needed to get to work on her report. She had wasted the whole day and only had one left to complete it. She sat down and began to work. Her mother wanted her to wash the dishes. Gina wished she hadn't wasted her day.

Jill convinced her boyfriend Joe to go look for Geocache with her. He didn't think it sounded like fun but decided to humor her. They searched the location where the Geocache was supposed to be. After over an hour of searching they were unable to find it. Jill hoped they would find it soon.

Bernice always wanted to travel to Africa. Bernice decided she would take a trip for her birthday next year. Bernice started to look at the price of airline tickets for the trip. In addition, Bernice looked up the price of hotels as well. Bernice decided to get an airplane ticket and reserve a room.

Joe and his friends had their soccer game today. Joe was nervous. He was nervous if he would win or not. Finally after the game, Joe's team won. Joe was very proud of his team.

David has always dreamed of visiting Oregon. Although he doesn't have much money, he starts saving a little. Finally David has enough money for his big trip to Oregon. On his trip, he eats local food and sees amazing sights. He has a great time in Oregon.

Lester has always wanted to be more artistic. He decides to try to draw a picture of a flower one day. He sits in front of a beautiful orchid and begins to draw. Lester's drawing comes out very well. He hangs the picture on the wall in his living room.

Jimmy went skateboarding this afternoon. It was the third time this week. He's getting good at it and really likes it. He fell once but hasn't given up. After all his practice this week, Jimmy has learned a new trick.

Keira found a man she thought was a keeper. He had a great job, impressive house, and paid for all their dates. A few months into dating, Keira started planning her wedding dress. And then he hit her because she burned dinner. Keira cannot stay with this abusive man.

Oliva wanted to go shopping. She decided to go to the mall. She found a great sale on shoes. She bought three pairs. Oliva had a great day shopping.

Jose is an immigrant. He and his family came here from Mexico. Jose wants to take a trip to visit his other family members Mexico. He plans diligently and purchases the necessary travel items. Jose take the trip to Mexico.

Oscar headed over to the nursery to find a tree to plant in his yard. He had a hard time deciding which tree to get. There were a lot of trees to go through. Finally, he opted on a Bonsai tree. It went perfectly with his home decor.
